"9f32d1d33b22ffa047a749fa9a39c282c5739740ad5406671919fd3fedde3aa9", "ref_doc_id": "b5b3a9af-ba89-485b-a6aa-1cc500c5b274"}, "6ead8d76-3678-431b-9aed-025ba45f10b4": {"doc_hash": "9b3d177667d174516934b493d437a207c8d616f8de4d3ec9983ed4823c784442", "ref_doc_id": "f48f78dd-3e54-4abe-b042-e2b50be4f540"}, "4176659c-6dcb-4b50-b860-7b36ca3f709c": {"doc_hash": "9786db1c0e9971e33e327c022068e063288034d19ec871a2afcea82c99bd8d27", "ref_doc_id": "1bb327f0-1941-4d9a-bbd1-fb4e51d9f465"}, "0e6948e3-d727-49f7-9fcd-294737321f48": {"doc_hash": "2ff602b8f59d7562377b55185e6b44c0fa1eac35a784a1dc2fffafde7ab43ffd", "ref_doc_id": "fb41ed02-0bc5-45db-b1e3-1f4a3c2c32fd"}, "cbe86898-d4d8-4532-9d52-ec214134eb05": {"doc_hash": "1b66c3ac26a45fead6b6792b278ebcd809d4dacd9c6aee0d4cd3fd238b3714e3", "ref_doc_id": "f0b8043c-805e-45ac-aaf2-bda14f7004a6"}, "e6e3d250-3fc2-4b12-b4e8-3f160032699d": {"doc_hash": "4e057d154efc795f7afe80020e36164ba6a38036ff779c693e0d49dd168a0a41", "ref_doc_id": "df58f08d-9170-4e5e-afb2-129e4187b06f"}}, "docstore/ref_doc_info": {"0dd2ea71-3671-46a1-ad5e-8f759dc725a0": {"node_ids": ["d639544c-2d14-4eac-bb30-e5fef91fd603"], "metadata": {"passage_id": 0}}, "458189c2-a1a6-458b-8ada-3567fe5ee842": {"node_ids": ["00ca38f4-e409-4bd7-bf15-e23c39f3e0a2"], "metadata": {"passage_id": 1}}, "eed65204-4121-4417-91ff-ce7ca982f908": {"node_ids": ["beb7651b-010c-4671-b337-8aa6a082321e"], "metadata": {"passage_id": 2}}, "553ede23-2ff9-4daf-b96c-9edf3bc29951": {"node_ids": ["6c571c08-edf4-4510-98df-f4c859da65c5"], "metadata": {"passage_id": 3}}, "b5b3a9af-ba89-485b-a6aa-1cc500c5b274": {"node_ids": ["ca291779-db89-4688-ae11-8b44ca920ac7"], "metadata": {"passage_id": 4}}, "f48f78dd-3e54-4abe-b042-e2b50be4f540": {"node_ids": ["6ead8d76-3678-431b-9aed-025ba45f10b4"], "metadata": {"passage_id": 5}}, "1bb327f0-1941-4d9a-bbd1-fb4e51d9f465": {"node_ids": ["4176659c-6dcb-4b50-b860-7b36ca3f709c"], "metadata": {"passage_id": 6}}, "fb41ed02-0bc5-45db-b1e3-1f4a3c2c32fd": {"node_ids": ["0e6948e3-d727-49f7-9fcd-294737321f48"], "metadata": {"passage_id": 7}}, "f0b8043c-805e-45ac-aaf2-bda14f7004a6": {"node_ids": ["cbe86898-d4d8-4532-9d52-ec214134eb05"], "metadata": {"passage_id": 8}}, "df58f08d-9170-4e5e-afb2-129e4187b06f": {"node_ids": ["e6e3d250-3fc2-4b12-b4e8-3f160032699d"], "metadata": {"passage_id": 9}}}, "docstore/data": {"d639544c-2d14-4eac-bb30-e5fef91fd603": {"__data__": {"id_": "d639544c-2d14-4eac-bb30-e5fef91fd603", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"passage_id": 0}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "0dd2ea71-3671-46a1-ad5e-8f759dc725a0", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"passage_id": 0}, "hash": "0448fba6935f871f266cdc07dda1757ef6e7e12155c52e981a58dbd7b11c4c2a", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "Uruguay (official full name in  ; pron.  , Eastern Republic of  Uruguay) is a country located in the southeastern part of South America.  It is home to 3.3 million people, of which 1.7 million live in the capital Montevideo and its metropolitan area.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 0, "end_char_idx": 250, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "00ca38f4-e409-4bd7-bf15-e23c39f3e0a2": {"__data__": {"id_": "00ca38f4-e409-4bd7-bf15-e23c39f3e0a2", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"passage_id": 1}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "458189c2-a1a6-458b-8ada-3567fe5ee842", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"passage_id": 1}, "hash": "99d412d95ac047bcb2417e9a01c35bf47dc8b6bd8a79051fa43658889738e956", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "It is bordered by Brazil to the north, by Argentina across the bank of both the Uruguay River to the west and the estuary of R\u00c3\u00ado de la Plata to the southwest, and the South Atlantic Ocean to the southeast. It is the second smallest independent country in South America, larger only than Suriname and the French overseas department of French Guiana.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 0, "end_char_idx": 349, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "beb7651b-010c-4671-b337-8aa6a082321e": {"__data__": {"id_": "beb7651b-010c-4671-b337-8aa6a082321e", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"passage_id": 2}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "eed65204-4121-4417-91ff-ce7ca982f908", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"passage_id": 2}, "hash": "10b11e9c77cdf06ab919f6f24aa0a2aa012a4edd86bcd4308793a4ff978380e9", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "Montevideo was founded by the Spanish in the early 18th century as a military stronghold. Uruguay won its independence in 1828 following a three-way struggle between Spain, Argentina and Brazil. It is a constitutional democracy, where the president fulfills the roles of both head of state and head of government", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 0, "end_char_idx": 312, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "6c571c08-edf4-4510-98df-f4c859da65c5": {"__data__": {"id_": "6c571c08-edf4-4510-98df-f4c859da65c5", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"passage_id": 3}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "553ede23-2ff9-4daf-b96c-9edf3bc29951", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"passage_id": 3}, "hash": "6e006870ba051c1c24cc627b3bfe20710e6feffe47b2ebd7708bfc24a0fa7e13", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "The economy is largely based in agriculture (making up 10% of the GDP and the most substantial export) and the state-sector, and relies heavily on world trade. Consequently, it is badly affected by any downturn in global prices. However, the economy is on the whole more stable than surrounding states, and it maintains a solid reputation with investors.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 0, "end_char_idx": 354, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "ca291779-db89-4688-ae11-8b44ca920ac7": {"__data__": {"id_": "ca291779-db89-4688-ae11-8b44ca920ac7", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"passage_id": 4}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "b5b3a9af-ba89-485b-a6aa-1cc500c5b274", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"passage_id": 4}, "hash": "8c56da175bf990ae626588d9f26c8b25b21e446b870613b5468b01092e3f0d00", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "According to Transparency International, Uruguay is the second least corrupt country in Latin America (after Chile),  Transparency.org.  with its political and labor conditions being among the freest on the continent.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 0, "end_char_idx": 217, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "6ead8d76-3678-431b-9aed-025ba45f10b4": {"__data__": {"id_": "6ead8d76-3678-431b-9aed-025ba45f10b4", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"passage_id": 5}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "f48f78dd-3e54-4abe-b042-e2b50be4f540", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"passage_id": 5}, "hash": "56e21344788dbab0d5302c890d6271e4e982efd636526c7b3f6d1de8da0cbdff", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "In November 2007 it became the first Latin American country and the second in the American Continent to recognize same-sex civil unions at the national level.   Uruguay Passes Civil-Union Law at  San Francisco Bay Times (December 6, 2007)", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 0, "end_char_idx": 238, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "4176659c-6dcb-4b50-b860-7b36ca3f709c": {"__data__": {"id_": "4176659c-6dcb-4b50-b860-7b36ca3f709c", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"passage_id": 6}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "1bb327f0-1941-4d9a-bbd1-fb4e51d9f465", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"passage_id": 6}, "hash": "f7fb34e514d94050e4da5c9fb42ab00c13c312e580ba70d32365042917ae331e", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "88% of the population are of European descent. Just under two-thirds of the population are declared Roman Catholics. However, the majority of Uruguayans are only nominally religious.  CIA World Factbook -- Uruguay", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 0, "end_char_idx": 213, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "0e6948e3-d727-49f7-9fcd-294737321f48": {"__data__": {"id_": "0e6948e3-d727-49f7-9fcd-294737321f48", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"passage_id": 7}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "fb41ed02-0bc5-45db-b1e3-1f4a3c2c32fd", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"passage_id": 7}, "hash": "b6765ad4299e49a41d42601722e6e716e10a3c2d7e9cb96cd3c5a779b3aa77d0", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "The name \"Uruguay\" comes from Guaran\u00c3\u00ad. It has many possible meanings. Some of the proposed meanings are:", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 0, "end_char_idx": 105, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "cbe86898-d4d8-4532-9d52-ec214134eb05": {"__data__": {"id_": "cbe86898-d4d8-4532-9d52-ec214134eb05", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"passage_id": 8}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "f0b8043c-805e-45ac-aaf2-bda14f7004a6", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"passage_id": 8}, "hash": "1dc3c41f1475324dbd5388eedf2b68718993a06f93c85a1cbaaf3a451e02c5a5", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "* \"River of colorful or 'painted' chinchillas (birds)\": poetic interpretation attributed to Juan Zorrilla de San Mart\u00c3\u00adn.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 0, "end_char_idx": 121, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "e6e3d250-3fc2-4b12-b4e8-3f160032699d": {"__data__": {"id_": "e6e3d250-3fc2-4b12-b4e8-3f160032699d", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"passage_id": 9}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "df58f08d-9170-4e5e-afb2-129e4187b06f", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"passage_id": 9}, "hash": "df807e670ed967fb4e5e3c80dcc02d23f2ed5ede816eb487f3dc02f0365018d4", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "* \"River of those who bring food\": an anonymous version which has been popularized since the discovery of an old document written by Jesuit Lucas Marton.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 0, "end_char_idx": 153, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}}}